WEBVTT

00:01.201 --> 00:02.874
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:02.936 --> 00:06.850
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:06.907 --> 00:08.716
the police
who investigate crime

00:08.775 --> 00:11.654
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:11.712 --> 00:13.385
These are their stories.

00:14.314 --> 00:15.588
Nice trip, Mr. Grobman?

00:15.649 --> 00:17.822
Too short, Rudy.
Is there any mail?

00:17.885 --> 00:20.263
Oh, yes, sir. And a
package from the court.

00:20.320 --> 00:23.028
Well, make sure my wife gets that
when she comes up from the garage.

00:23.090 --> 00:24.467
Oh, sure thing.

00:24.525 --> 00:26.004
(GUNSHOTS)

00:26.059 --> 00:27.436
(TIRES SCREECHING)

00:28.862 --> 00:30.364
GROBMAN:
Oh, my God! God!

00:30.430 --> 00:32.671
Call 911. Call!

00:33.400 --> 00:35.380
Denise! Denise!

00:36.970 --> 00:38.677
All I saw, Judge
Grobman was wounded,

00:38.739 --> 00:40.241
and that car was
fishtailing out of here.

00:40.307 --> 00:42.116
Brand new Jaguar XJR.

00:42.709 --> 00:45.588
And did you see anybody hangin'
around here before it happened?

00:45.646 --> 00:47.523
Nobody who didn't belong.

00:47.581 --> 00:49.925
She's a nice lady.
She gonna be okay?

00:49.983 --> 00:51.758
I hope so.
Thanks for your help.

00:52.553 --> 00:54.123
Which hospital?
St. Marks.

00:54.187 --> 00:56.133
Husband went with her in the ambulance.
Any witnesses?

00:56.189 --> 00:58.601
Not that we know of. We got the
car info from the doorman,

00:58.659 --> 01:01.139
APB went out maybe seven minutes
after shots were fired.

01:01.194 --> 01:04.766
Okay, thanks. Canvass the tenants and see
if there's anybody we need to talk to.

01:04.831 --> 01:07.607
Victim's Denise Grobman,
civil court judge.

01:07.668 --> 01:10.239
She and her husband have lived
here for nine years and change.

01:10.304 --> 01:12.614
Polite but not chatty.
Husband's an architect.

01:12.673 --> 01:13.743
What do you got?

01:13.807 --> 01:17.084
Victim went down, here. .38's hers.
Two rounds fired.

01:17.144 --> 01:18.953
ED: Civil court judge
needs a gun?

01:19.012 --> 01:20.821
Maybe she hands
out too much alimony.

01:20.881 --> 01:22.189
You find the slugs?

01:22.249 --> 01:24.195
No. Blood over here
can't be hers.

01:24.251 --> 01:26.993
She might've hit him two
out of two, good shooting.

01:27.054 --> 01:29.034
Fair. Good would be
him layin' here dead.

01:29.089 --> 01:32.400
And over here, we have
three cigarette butts.

01:32.459 --> 01:35.531
ED: So, guy waited here
for the first opportunity.

01:35.596 --> 01:39.066
Fuse box is open. Maybe it
was an electrician working.

01:39.132 --> 01:40.805
Maybe. Dust it anyway.

01:40.867 --> 01:42.471
Yeah. No problem.

01:42.536 --> 01:46.006
APB went out quick, if the
car-jacker's got two gunshot wounds,

01:46.073 --> 01:48.212
how far can he get?
I'm feelin' lucky.

01:48.275 --> 01:50.619
Last time I got lucky was 1986.

01:50.677 --> 01:52.623
It's all in the
attitude, Lennie.

01:54.000 --> 02:00.074
